article.headline: San Diego St. 70, Air Force 48
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Freshman Kawhi Leonard scored 15 points to lead San Diego State to a 70-48 win over Air Force on Tuesday night. Malcolm Thomas added 10 points and 12 rebounds as the Aztecs (16-6, 5-3 Mountain West) raised their home record to 24-6 against the Falcons. Reserve Kelvin Davis scored 12 points. The Aztecs, who have won four of five, held Air Force scoreless for nearly the first 10 minutes. By the time the Falcons scored their first points, San Diego State led only 12-2 because it had missed 15 of 20 shots. The Aztecs, who had a 26-17 halftime lead, led the entire game. Grant Parker had 14 points and Tom Fow 11 to lead Air Force (9-12, 1-7), which snapped a 22-game conference losing streak by beating Wyoming on Saturday. Parker hit 3 of 6 3-pointers, while Fow made all three of his 3-point attempts.
